column30: A copy of the letter we sent in to our MP & MPP. Good afternoon, I am one of your constituents in Stittsville and wanted to write to you in order to inform you of at least one """"ground level"""" story of how the lockdowns are affecting the public. My family is struggling already and I don't know if another lockdown period is going to be sustainable. My wife and I both work for the federal government and have been rather unaffected by the lockdowns income-wise, luckily, however the school and other closures are taking a huge toll on my children. I have two in high school and one in grade 6 and all of them have seen their social circles evaporate in the past two years. The lockdown has hit them socially extremely hard as they struggled making friends beforehand, but now they all have none. I try to get them to enter other activities however everything is closed. Each time we start gaining momentum, we get the rug pulled out from under us. They have lost their drive and they are always sad. All have developed anxiety issues and are now seeing counsellors, their grades are suffering and we are struggling more and more to keep them moving forward in life. My eldest in particular has lost half of grade nine, all of grade 10 and it looks like all of grade 11. She will have lost her entire high school life and lost all social contacts being locked in her room by society order. I don't think that we can handle another lockdown. Several times a week we are consoling at least one of them as they cry themselves to sleep. My children NEED to be able to go to school and develop socially. We need help! To be clear I'm not an internet troll anti-vaxxer, we are all fully vaccinated. I fail to understand with all the research coming out that the omicron variant is far less serious than the original covid virus, why we are being pushed to the breaking point again. I know the story that the hospitals *might* be overwhelmed, but from my standpoint it seems like my family and I are being forced to *actually* suffer so that someone else *might* not. We keep being told to """"suck it up"""" but we've been doing everything *right* this whole time but the finish line keeps getting moved further and further away and we have reached our breaking point. Even my entire extended family is becoming quite extremist and it's scary. My uncles, aunts and cousins are turning anti-vax, crowing about 5G and Q-anon conspiracy theories and they are getting louder. These restrictions are causing something very ugly to bubble to the surface in our society. Please, we need your help to make our voices heard. Best Regards, Giles Babin and Family
Anti Vax Mom!!!

column1: Moms looking for work from home jobs in Georgia
column30: Hey guys. As a mom I have started a new business. I am looking for someone who is willing to help me cover outbound cold calls Monday-Friday. I am flexible. You can pick the hours you work daily. I get being a parent! I have a toddler and am expecting in April. (Thats why I need help with calls-my house is far from quiet!) Requirements: -comfortable on the phone or willing to learn. -you will need a smartphone to be able to access our phone dialing app. -ability to adapt to each phone call. This will not be traditional sales. I will train you personally with how I like calls handled. -WiFi or cell service with data. -CashApp or PayPal to receive payments weekly. -a quiet work space. -available anytime between 8am-6pm EST to make calls based on time zones. -an email address to receive work. -willing to work alone at your own pace and keep in communication regularly with me. -a positive attitude. -must be in the USA and speak fluent English. Not required: -No COVID vax required. You are working remotely and your health is your personal choice. I have no right to enforce something like this on you. -computer or laptop. This will make life easier on you, but you can do everything from you phone. -experience. Its a plus, but not required. I am looking for something altogether different when it comes to call handling. These will not be rushed calls, but rather really getting to know the customer and their needs so that we can help them grow as well. The position will be long term with bonuses per contract that you close. It will be contract hourly without additional benefits. There will be a 2 week trial period for all new team members. Starting pay is $4/hour (including training) plus bonuses monthly at 1% or the total monthly account value for the first full 3 months of the account longevity. Raises are a big possibility as we grow. Minimum 10 hours per week, but you can work as much as you would like if there are contacts to reach out to. Please comment if you are interested and Ill message you.

CEBU CITY, Philippines  Minors aged 15 years and below can now go out in Cebu City provided they are accompanied by fully vaccinated guardians. This was the pronouncement of Acting Mayor Michael Rama as signified in the new Directive 10-25-01 setting the guidelines for the implementation of the Alert Level 2 quarantine status in the city. Generally, the stay-at-home order remains for minors below 15 years old, senior citizens above 65 years old, and people with comorbidities or pre-existing medical conditions, except for obtaining essential goods and services, for work, and other permitted activities. Since the last Executive Order, senior citizens above 65 years old may already go out as long as they are fully vaccinated. This time, the Cebu City government has allowed minors below 15 years old to also enjoy the opening of more establishments in the city, and the policy also serves as a prelude to the eventual return of the face-to-face classes. Subject to other legal restrictions, minors and children who are below 15 years of age may be allowed in authorized establishments. Provided that they must be accompanied and supervised by a parent, guardian, or responsible adult. Minors need not be accompanied for purposes of obtaining essential goods and services, stated the directive. Furthermore, minors can enter authorized establishments such as indoor dining, as long as they are accompanied by a fully vaccinated guardian.

Was anyone here vaccinated as a minor without the consent of their anti-vax parents? If so, what inspired you to do so? Id love to hear from you! Personally, I dont have anti-vaccine parents, but I work to support teens that do, and I recently published an op-ed in the LA Times on this issue. Im the founder of VaxTeen, which was inspired by stories of teenagers with anti-vaccine parents turning to Reddit. Its website allows teens to determine what vaccines they need and when they can receive them without parental consent in their state. VaxTeen communicates directly with teenagers and young adults to educate them on the importance of vaccines and empower them to make well-informed decisions about their health.
